The '''Citizen Option for Macedonia''' ({{lang-mk|Граѓанска опција за Македонија-ГРОМ}}, ''Graǵanska оpcija za Makedonija'', '''GROM''' (lit. "Thunder")) is a [[List of political parties in the Republic of Macedonia|political party]] in [[North Macedonia]] led by [[Stevčo Jakimovski]], mayor of [[Karpoš Municipality|Karpoš]].

==History==
The party was established by Jakimovski in May 2013 after he left the [[Social Democratic Union of Macedonia|Social Democratic Union]] in protest at its planned boycott of the [[2013 Macedonian local elections|2013 local elections]].<ref>[http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/citizens-option-for-macedonia-grom Citizens Option for Macedonia, GROM] Balkan Insight, 21 March 2014</ref> It nominated [[Zoran T. Popovski]] as its presidential candidate for the [[2014 Macedonian general election|2014 general elections]], with Popovski finishing fourth out of four candidates with 3.61% of the vote.

In the parliamentary elections GROM led an alliance under its own name, including the [[Liberal Party of Macedonia|Liberal Party]], the [[Serbian Progressive Party in Macedonia]], the [[Union of Tito's Left Forces]], and the Party of Free 
Democrats.<ref>[http://www.kas.de/wf/doc/kas_37896-1522-1-30.pdf?140529150937  The Republic of Macedonia's 2014 Parliamentary Elections Handbook] Konrad Adenauer Stiftung</ref> The alliance received 2.8% of the vote, winning one seat in the [[Assembly of the Republic of Macedonia|Assembly]].<ref>[http://www.electionguide.org/elections/id/2781/ Macedonia] IFES</ref>

